<TITLE> Army puts death toll at 3,447 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 20 (bdnews24.com)The death toll due to Cyclone Sidr officially reached 3,447 at 11 am Tuesday, the Bangladesh Army disaster management wing reported. The number of injured stood at 3,322, and the missing numbered 1,063, the army's DMW stated. An estimated 32.73 lakh people, of more than 9 lakh families, have been rendered homeless in the disaster. Ripening crops standing on about 8.72 lakh acres of land have been totally or partially destroyed. The cyclone wrought this damage in 968 union parishads of 133 upazilas under 20 coastal districts. The number of wholly or partly damaged educational institutions total 4,993, which are all closed now. Of the local roads, 58 km have been totally destroyed and about 88,000 km of roads have been partly ruined. Damage to embankments run to 57 km, while 3.5 lakh trees have been destroyed. bdnews2
